page.title: 13TREES
page.content:
Trees in Dorset mainly consist of deciduous trees but conifers pop up here and there.Here is a list of the trees in this area.
DECIDUOUS--Ash,Oak,Willow,Holly, horthorn,Hazel,Damzen,Sloe,Acorn, Maple,Chesnut(Sweet,Horse),Birch, elder,Sycamore,elm,Plum,Beech,Cherry, Apple,Mulberry,Alder. CONIFER--Scotts pine,Larch,Spruce, cedar,yew. Trees are found in patches,woods,copses and occaisonally in lines making rivers look like avenues.Willows and elders are often found by water and marshy ground.Woods drain moisture and goodness out of the ground,and with lots of wooded area, Doret,thanks to the woods has a lot of scrub.Although trees do alot for animals they are destroyed for farming
